Recommends: gstreamer1.0-icamerasrc
Description: On-demand LED control for Intel IPU7 cameras
 Manages the camera LED on Intel IPU7 devices (ThinkPad X1 2-in-1 Gen 10
 and similar Lunar Lake systems) so it lights up only when an application
 is actively using the camera.
 .
 A single GStreamer process holds a dual-source pipeline: videotestsrc feeds
 black frames while idle; icamerasrc is started on demand when an application
 opens the camera and shut down (LED off) when it stops.
 .
 The virtual camera device /dev/video32 ("IPU7 Camera") is visible to Zoom
 and other V4L2-based applications. A PipeWire node is also published for
 Flatpak and portal-based applications (Brave, Signal, Telegram).
 .
 Requires icamerasrc and the Intel IPU7 Camera HAL to be installed separately.
